# Routes

Routes **only**:

- Mount paths under `/api/*` (see `server.js`)
- Attach middleware (`protect`, `express-validator` rules)
- Map HTTP method + path → controller handler

## REST conventions

- `GET /api/users` — list
- `POST /api/users` — create
- `PUT /api/users/:id` — update
- `DELETE /api/users/:id` — delete

Use consistent, predictable naming. **Do not** add duplicate or unnecessary endpoints.

## Example (this project)

```javascript
// routes/auth.js — validation + handler wiring only
router.post("/register", registerValidation, register);
router.get("/me", protect, getMe);
```

Validation rules (`body()`, etc.) belong in routes. Registration/login **logic** belongs in services, called from thin controllers.
